{
  "stem": "19690.3",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "If we wanted to be out overnight, we had to get a pass.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "During the day, we could come and go as we wished.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And that's how we then went to the consulate and got our papers processed again.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "Then my father would come in on the trolley from [INAUDIBLE] Provence near camp.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "He would have to walk about 30 minutes to the nearest tram and then take the tram and come into town.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And he would stay at a hotel nearby that we would make reservations for.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "And this was a time when we would all stay at the hotel and get an overnight pass while we can.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Till 1942 in the summer.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In Gurs, I do not remember any religious things being done.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "When we got to Marseille, there was another hotel nearby called Hotel [INAUDIBLE], and there they had services every Friday and on the holidays.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we would participate there, as best-- as often as we could.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I don't know about my father at Le Milles.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I don't know that.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But my mother and I would go whenever we could and participate in the service.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "It was ultra orthodox, which is not what we were used to.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And for me as a child, it was rather boring.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But it was services and we went.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Then in the beginning of 1942, I started preparing for my bar mitzvah and I was put in touch with a rabbi who headed a more conservative synagogue.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "It was not a synagogue, it was a-- a prayer room in a storefront kind of thing.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And he taught me my [HEBREW], my Torah portion, and helped me to sing, which was a major project.",
      "word_count": 19
    }
  ],
